HTML Reference

	MDN (Mozila Developers Network)

		All syntax & grammar rules.

		Best thing to use as a reference.


	Reasons to use the right tags:

		Content might not render.

		Accesibility devices need it.

		Web crawlers use them for SEO


	Most common tags:

		Heading elements: <h1> Heading 1 </h1>
						  <h2> Heading 2 </h2>
						  <h3> Heading 3 </h3>
						  <h4> Heading 4 </h4>
						  <h5> Heading 5 </h5>
						  <h6> Heading 6 </h6>

		Paragraph tag: <p> Paragraph here </p>

		Span tag: <span> small text here </span>

		Preserve whitespace: <pre> dont use this </pre>

		Hyperlink: <a href="www.ios.com"> Click here </a> 

		Unordered list: <ul>
		                  <li>Item1</li>
		                  <li>Item2</li>
		                </ul>

		Ordered list: <ol>
		                  <li>Item1</li>
		                  <li>Item2</li>
		              </ol>

		Divider: <div> text </div> // Used a lot in react

		Section: <section> </section>

		Article: <article> </article>

		Sidebar or extra content: <aside> </aside> // ads uses

		Header: <header> </header>

		Footer: <footer> </footer>

		<br> Creates space. Dont use. </br>

		<hr> Creates a line. Dont use. </hr>

		<em> Looks italizized </em>

		<strong> Looks bold </strong>

		* We choose types for accesibility, not for style. 

		Depricated tags:

			<bold> </bold>
			<italic> </italic>



